      "repair_reason": "- [P1] Needs maintainer/security policy review and contributor real-run proof before automation can safely help; the diagnostic gap is concrete but not the only blocker.; Needs attention: The diff changes which local directory can supply prompt instructions and safety rules, so the prompt-authority boundary needs maintainer approval and proof.; Review finding: [P2] Pass the default agent id into bootstrap diagnostic... (sha=8df20895874a199152aa84368f71028b19b0c348)",
      "review_summary": "The PR changes agent bootstrap resolution to merge files from an explicitly configured per-agent `agentDir` with workspace bootstrap files, with `agentDir` files taking precedence.\n\nPR surface: Source +30. Total +30 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. by source inspection: current main loads bootstrap files from `workspaceDir` and does not read configured `agentDir` before prompt context is built. I have not run a live OpenClaw session in this read-only review.",
