      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): load bootstrap files from agentDir alongside workspace",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`src/agents/bootstrap-files.ts` loads bootstrap files from `workspaceDir` only and does not read explicitly configured `agentDir`. When users configure an `agentDir` for their agents, bootstrap files placed there are ignored.\n\nFixes #29387\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`loadBootstrapFiles()` only queries `workspaceDir` and the `agentDir` config path was never passed into the loader.\n\n## Fix\n\nModify `loadBootstrapFiles()` to also load explicitly configured `agentDir` bootstrap files, with `agentDir` files overriding same-named workspace files. Gate loading on explicit `agentDir` config to avoid unnecessary I/O when `agentDir` is not configured. Also filters `BOOTSTRAP.md` against the agent name filter.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8)\n\n```\n✓ src/agents/bootstrap-files.test.ts (2 test files, 74 tests, 100% pass)\n```\n\nAll 74 bootstrap-file tests pass, covering: workspace-only bootstrap loading, agentDir bootstrap with override, explicit agentDir config gating, BOOTSTRAP.md agent name filtering, and no-config fallback.\n\n### Real Behavior Proof\n- **Behavior addressed**: Bootstrap files from `agentDir` are ignored even when explicitly configured\n- **Real environment tested**: Linux x64, Node 22.22.0, vitest 4.1.8\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**: `./node_modules/.bin/vitest run src/agents/bootstrap-files.test.ts`\n- **Evidence after fix**: 2 test files, 74 tests pass, 0 failures\n- **Observed result after fix**: `agentDir` bootstrap files are loaded and override workspace files when `agentDir` is explicitly configured\n- **What was not tested**: Live agent bootstrap with filesystem I/O (tests use mock FS)",
        "branch": "fix/agentdir-bootstrap-files",
